---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services · Pro Se Fair Play Mediation"
  description="Professional family mediation and court-ready family law document preparation for self-represented individuals in Florida."
>
  <!-- ========================== HEADER ========================== -->
  <header class="svc-overview-header">
    <div class="container svc-overview-header-inner">
      <p class="kicker reveal reveal-d1">
        <span class="kicker-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        Services
      </p>
      <h1 class="display svc-overview-title reveal reveal-d2">
        Family <span class="display-italic">Mediation</span>.
        <br />Court-Ready <span class="display-italic">Documents</span>.
      </h1>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ========================== BODY ========================== -->
  <section class="svc-overview-body">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="display svc-overview-h2">Family Mediation</h2>

      <p>
        I provide professional family mediation services designed to
        help families navigate difficult transitions in a structured,
        respectful, and supportive environment. My goal is to help
        parties work toward practical and meaningful resolutions
        outside of the courtroom whenever possible while reducing
        unnecessary conflict, emotional stress, and financial strain
        on the family.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a neutral mediator, my role is to facilitate productive
        communication, keep discussions focused and organized, and
        help both parties navigate sensitive conversations with
        professionalism. I understand that no two families are alike,
        and every situation deserves thoughtful attention.
      </p>
      <p>
        Mediation gives parents the opportunity to remain in control
        of the decisions that will impact their lives and the
        well-being of their children, rather than placing those
        important decisions entirely in the hands of the court.
        Through a calm and structured process, families are able to
        work toward solutions that reflect their unique needs,
        priorities, and long-term goals while creating a healthier
        path forward for everyone involved.
      </p>

      <h2 class="display svc-overview-h2">Court-Ready Family Law Documents</h2>

      <p>
        In addition to mediation services, I assist self-represented
        individuals with the preparation and completion of
        professionally organized, court-ready family law documents.
        My document preparation services are designed to provide
        clients with a more structured, efficient, and organized
        approach to navigating the family court process during what
        is often a very stressful and emotional time.
      </p>
      <p>
        I offer two primary document preparation services tailored to
        the specific needs of family law clients.
      </p>

      <h3 class="display svc-overview-h3">Parenting Plan Preparation</h3>

      <p>
        For parents who need assistance preparing only a Parenting
        Plan, I provide professionally customized parenting plans
        tailored to the unique needs and schedules of each family.
        These plans may address important issues such as time-sharing
        schedules, holidays, transportation, parental responsibility,
        communication guidelines, and child support provisions.
      </p>
      <p>
        This service is limited strictly to the preparation of the
        Parenting Plan document itself and does not include
        additional court forms or filing services. Clients are
        responsible for filing the completed Parenting Plan with the
        court independently.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every Parenting Plan is prepared with close attention to
        structure, clarity, organization, and procedural detail to
        help families create a practical framework centered around
        the best interests of their children.
      </p>

      <h3 class="display svc-overview-h3">Turnkey Family Law Document Preparation</h3>

      <p>
        For clients seeking a more comprehensive solution, I offer a
        premium Turnkey Family Law Document Preparation Service
        designed for self-represented individuals who want their
        family law paperwork professionally organized, fully prepared,
        and ready for filing.
      </p>
      <p>
        This service includes the preparation and completion of the
        mandatory family court forms and supporting documents
        required for filing family law matters, including financial
        affidavits, parenting plans, child support documentation,
        settlement agreements, supplemental petitions, and other
        court-required filings as applicable to the client's case.
      </p>
      <p>
        Documents are professionally organized, fully prepared, and
        notarized when required, providing clients with a streamlined
        experience designed to minimize confusion and reduce the
        stress often associated with navigating the court system
        independently. The goal of this service is to allow clients
        to walk into the courthouse with professionally prepared,
        court-ready documents that are organized and ready to file.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every matter is handled with professionalism, discretion,
        care, and exceptional attention to detail to ensure clients
        feel informed, prepared, and supported throughout the
        process.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================== CTA ========================== -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container-narrow cta-inner">
      <p class="kicker cta-kicker">Not sure where to start?</p>
      <h2 class="display cta-title">
        Find out if one of these is the
        <span class="display-italic">right fit</span>.
      </h2>
      <p class="lede cta-lede">
        A free 15-minute consultation. We'll review your situation
        and identify which service, if any, fits your case.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary cta-btn" href="/book">
          Book a Free Consultation
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ============================================================
     HEADER (photo hero — same pattern as book / faq / blog before)
     ============================================================ */
  .svc-overview-header {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: clamp(5rem, 7vw + 2rem, 8rem) clamp(3rem, 4vw + 1rem, 5rem);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    background-color: var(--color-navy-deep);
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(135deg,
        rgba(15, 27, 50, 0.9) 0%,
        rgba(27, 42, 74, 0.78) 50%,
        rgba(27, 42, 74, 0.9) 100%),
      url('/signdocs.jpeg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .svc-overview-header::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: auto 0 0 0;
    height: 4rem;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-cream));
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .svc-overview-header-inner { position: relative; max-width: 64rem; z-index: 1; }
  .svc-overview-header .kicker { color: var(--color-gold); }
  .svc-overview-header .kicker-dot {
    background: var(--color-gold);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 25%, transparent);
  }
  .svc-overview-title {
    font-size: var(--step-5);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    max-width: 22ch;
    font-weight: 400;
    text-shadow: 0 2px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
  }
  .svc-overview-title .display-italic {
    color: var(--color-gold);
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .svc-overview-header .lede {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 56ch;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-cream) 85%, transparent);
  }

  /* ============================================================
     BODY (long-form prose)
     ============================================================ */
  .svc-overview-body {
    padding-block: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-3xl);
    background: var(--color-cream);
  }
  .svc-overview-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .svc-overview-body p + p {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .svc-overview-h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    font-weight: 400;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
    position: relative;
  }
  .svc-overview-h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .svc-overview-h2::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: -1px; left: 0;
    width: 3rem; height: 1px;
    background: var(--color-gold);
  }
  .svc-overview-h3 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* ============================================================
     CTA (matches the pattern used on the deep service pages)
     ============================================================ */
  .cta {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: var(--space-3xl);
    background: var(--color-cream-warm);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    overflow: hidden;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
  }
  .cta::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0 0 auto 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--color-gold) 40%, var(--color-gold) 60%, transparent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .cta-kicker { color: var(--color-gold-deep); }
  .cta-title {
    margin-block: 1rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: var(--step-4);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .cta-title .display-italic { color: var(--color-gold-deep); }
  .cta-lede { color: var(--color-ink-soft); max-width: 56ch; }
  .cta-actions {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .cta-btn {
    background: var(--color-navy);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-navy);
  }
  .cta-btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-navy-deep);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .svc-overview-title {
      font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 1.8rem + 3vw, 3.5rem);
      max-width: 100%;
    }
    .svc-overview-h2 {
      font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 2vw, 2.25rem);
    }
    .svc-overview-h3 {
      font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 1.75rem);
    }
  }
</style>
